<Class name="CMIF_TableReportMarker" id="54f49e6c-aa79-4625-8556-5690bc5f28df">
    <superclass name="CMIF_Object"/>
    <transient/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>You'd use these in conjunction with the CM_GenericTablePrint form.

If you want a page break somewhere set the rows itemObject to be a CMIF_ReportpageEnd.

If you want report groups to stay together set the start/end rows itemObjects to be a CMIF_ReportGroupBegin/CMIF_ReportGroupEnd.  If the group
is less than a page in size it will start printing it on the next page rather than break it over two pages (helping to prevent widows and
orphans).</text>
    <DbClassMap file="cmtrans"/>
</Class>
